# Backend pre-commit: only operate on the backend repo.
#
# OpenAPI export + frontend contract sync (npm run openapi:commit) was removed
# from this hook: it reached into the sibling ../frontend repo and mutated it on
# every commit (api:sync:local, api:coverage, generate:capabilities), which is
# fragile and breaks for anyone without the frontend checked out.
#
# OpenAPI drift is already enforced in CI ("Check OpenAPI export drift" in
# .github/workflows/ci.yml). When you change the API surface, regenerate the
# contract explicitly before committing:
#   npm run openapi:export      # backend cache + frontend openapi.remote.json
#   npm run openapi:commit      # also runs the full frontend contract sync
npx lint-staged
